title: IGP: One suspect in Jong-nam murder suffered effects of VX agent
text:
More 
One of the two women suspected of killing the   Korea's leader with the highly toxic VX nerve agent also suffered its effects, Malaysia's police chief said today. 
"She was vomiting," Khalid Abu Bakar said in response to a question about whether the women felt the effects   Nations. 
He declined to elaborate. 
Kim Jong-nam   Police have arrested a Vietnamese woman and an Indonesian woman suspected of smearing the chemical on his face.
